# Trivy ignore list for known Netty CVEs that are pulled in transitively by Quarkus
# (quarkus-vertx -> quarkus-netty -> io.netty:*).
# These entries acknowledge the findings and mark them as accepted short-term while
# we plan an upstream upgrade of Quarkus or Netty to obtain fixed versions.

# io.netty:netty-codec-haproxy:4.1.133.Final (transitive via io.quarkus:quarkus-vertx -> io.quarkus:quarkus-netty)
# Issue: CVE-2026-44893 - HAProxy SSL TLV parsing leaks retained slice on invalid TLV length
# See: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-44893
CVE-2026-44893 exp:2026-06-30

# io.netty:netty-handler:4.1.133.Final (transitive via io.quarkus:quarkus-vertx -> io.quarkus:quarkus-netty)
# Issues:
#  - CVE-2026-44249 - IPv6 Subnet Filter Bypass via Incorrect Comparator Masking
#    See: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-44249
#  - CVE-2026-45416 - SNI handler pre-allocates up to 16 MiB from nine attacker bytes
#    See: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-45416
CVE-2026-44249 exp:2026-06-30
CVE-2026-45416 exp:2026-06-30

# io.netty:netty-resolver-dns:4.1.133.Final (transitive via io.quarkus:quarkus-vertx -> io.quarkus:quarkus-netty)
# Issues:
#  - CVE-2026-45674 - Vulnerable to DNS Cache Poisoning via Missing Bailiwick Checks in CNAME handling
#    See: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-45674
#  - CVE-2026-47691 - Insufficient Bailiwick Validation for NS Records
#    See: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-47691
CVE-2026-45674 exp:2026-06-30
CVE-2026-47691 exp:2026-06-30

# Historical/existing ignores retained
CVE-2026-42402 exp:2026-06-30
CVE-2026-42403 exp:2026-06-30
